  <prompt>
    Per spec FR-SC-01 and FR-SC-02, both components must be exported from the `@spaarke/ui-components` barrel `src/index.ts` so downstream consumers (Semantic Search PCF Tags filter task, Semantic Search PCF row menu task) can `import { TagFilter, DocumentRowMenu, TagFilterOption, IDocumentRowMenuTarget, DocumentRowAction } from '@spaarke/ui-components'`. This task updates the barrel only — both components must already exist (tasks 010 and 011 must be ✅ before starting). Verify the shared library builds clean and both consuming PCFs still build against the updated barrel.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Frontend developer comfortable with TypeScript barrel-export hygiene in `@spaarke/ui-components` and aware of the React 16/17 PCF compatibility constraint (ADR-022) for anything re-exported from this library.
  </role>

  <goal>
    `src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/index.ts` re-exports `TagFilter`, `DocumentRowMenu`, plus their public types (`TagFilterOption`, `IDocumentRowMenuTarget`, `DocumentRowAction`). The shared library builds clean. Both PCFs (Semantic Search + Visual Host) still build clean against the updated barrel.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Tasks 010 and 011 intentionally deferred barrel export to this task so that the barrel file is touched exactly once after both components exist, avoiding parallel-edit conflicts. This task is the gating step that makes both components consumable by the downstream PCF tasks (FR-DOC-01 row menu integration and FR-DOC-05 Tags filter integration).
    </background>
